02/10/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A parliamentary delegation starts a three-day visit to Slovakia on Thursday (2 October), the first by Bulgarian lawmakers since the 1993 split of the former Czechoslovakia.
National Assembly Chairman Ognyan Gerdzhikov is heading the delegation.
The talks will focus on bilateral economic and political ties and co-operation between the two countries in the context of their EU and NATO integration efforts.
Slovakia and Bulgaria are to join NATO next year.
(BTA, BNR - 02/10/03)
